description: MADRID- The Spanish government officially recognized the State of Palestine on May 28th following a decision adopted by the Council of Ministers. The decision was announced to the parliament by Prime Minister Pedro Sánchez.
title: Palestinians’ goals cannot be limited by ‘crumbs’ offered by two-state solution

description: TEHRAN - Public sentiments against Israel have been growing among Egyptian people since the Tel Aviv regime launched war on the Gaza Strip on October 7.
title: Anti-Israeli sentiment sweeping Egypt

description: TEHRAN - In a significant development for Iran's aviation industry, a knowledge-based company has achieved a major breakthrough by mastering the production of jet engine turbine blades, according to a report by the Tasnim News Agency.
title: Iran makes advancements in aviation industry as sanctions constrict access to equipment

description: TEHRAN - In an analysis, the Iran newspaper discussed the widespread coverage of the letter of the Leader of the Revolution in the international media and said: Upon the escalation and continuation of Israel's crimes against the oppressed Palestinian people, American and European universities have also become the scene of protest against the genocide of the Palestinian people by the Zionist regime.
title: You are standing on the right side of history

description: TEHRAN – The Deputy for Knowledge and Research of the Islamic Revolution Guard Corps (IRGC) Navy has emphasized that the true power of Iran extends beyond its military capabilities, highlighting the resilience in the nation’s spirit.
title: IRGC Navy official: Iran's strength lies beyond weaponry

description: TEHRAN – Iran and Qatar have once again called on regional and extra-regional countries to help bring an end to the plight of Palestinians in the besieged Gaza Strip who have been subject to brutal and savage Israeli attacks in the past 8 months.
title: Iran, Qatar renew call for Gaza ceasefire

description: TEHRAN– Bahrain has recently expressed its intention to significantly improve and strengthen its diplomatic relations with the Islamic Republic of Iran, signaling a proactive effort towards fostering a thaw in Bahrain-Iran relations.
title: Bahrain seeks to rekindle Iran ties

description: TEHRAN - In a strong rebuke, Iran has condemned the European Union's imposition of fresh sanctions against Iranian officials and entities, emphasizing the Islamic Republic's right to retaliate.
title: Iran condemns new European sanctions, says it reserves right to respond

description: TEHRAN– The International Summit on Gaza, titled “The Oppressed but Resilient,” commenced in Tehran on Saturday, drawing prominent political figures as it coincides with the 35th anniversary of Imam Khomeini's demise.
title: Tehran hosts international summit on Gaza

description: TEHRAN – Iranians are gearing up for the passing anniversary of Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini, the founder of the Islamic Republic of Iran, who passed away on June 3, 1989.
title: Imam Khomeini and Palestine: an everlasting legacy

description: TEHRAN- Hamas has said it views “positively” the content of U.S. President Joe Biden’s speech and is ready to deal with any  ceasefire proposal in a “constructive manner”.
title: Hamas views ceasefire proposal “positively”

description: TEHRAN - As the deadline for candidacy registration in Iran’s upcoming presidential election approaches, the nation is witnessing a notable surge in political activity.
title: Election fever on a gradual rise

description: TEHRAN– The spokesperson for the Constitutional Council, Hadi Tahan Nazif, has announced on Saturday the approval of amendments to the presidential election law and measures to enhance the transparency of the three branches of government.
title: Constitutional Council approves amendments to presidential election law

description: TEHRAN – Persepolis football team defeated Mes 1-0 on Saturday here at the Azadi Stadium to win 2023/24 Iran’s Persian Gulf Pro League (PGPL) for the ninth time.
title: Persepolis crowned PGPL champions for ninth time

description: Hundreds of people protesting Israel’s war in Gaza marched to the Brooklyn Museum Friday afternoon, set up tents in the lobby and unfurled a “Free Palestine” banner from the building’s roof before police moved in to make arrests.
title: New York police arrest pro-Palestinian demonstrators

description: Thousands of pro-Palestinian supporters held a mass demonstration on Saturday in front of the United States embassy on Jalan Medan Merdeka Selatan, Central Jakarta, condemning Israeli atrocities in the Rafah refugee camp.
title: Thousands rally in Jakarta to condemn Israeli atrocities

description: A Palestinian child starved to death on Saturday in the central Gaza Strip due to Israel’s ongoing blockade of the Rafah crossing, which has prevented humanitarian aid from entering for nearly a month.
title: Palestinian child dies of malnutrition

description: US President Joe Biden has said that his administration rejects the International Criminal Court’s (ICC) application for arrest warrants against Israeli leaders, saying there is “no equivalence between Israel and Hamas”.
title: Biden claims Israel’s war on Gaza not genocide

description: Fighters from the Lebanese Hezbollah resistance movement have intercepted and shot down an Israeli unmanned aerial vehicle as it was flying in the skies over southern Lebanon.
title: Hezbollah shoots down Israeli drone

description: TEHRAN - A group of tourists hailing from different nations have toured Esfahak, a historical village in eastern Iran, aligning with underway efforts to secure its status as a Global Tourism Village.
title: Esfahak hosts overseas tourists amid global village bid

description: TEHRAN - Foreign passenger entries through the Nordooz border, located in Aras Free Zone, have surged by 55% in the course of the last Persian year (ended in March 2024).
title: Foreign passenger entries spike by 55% at Nordooz Border

description: TEHRAN – Ali Darabi has advocated for the inclusion of “Cultural Heritage” courses in Iran’s national curriculum, aiming to deepen students’ connection to their heritage.
title: Push for cultural heritage education in Iran’s curriculum

description: TEHRAN - Persepolis, Iran’s crown jewel of ancient civilization, has opened its gates to the world with the launch of a comprehensive website and an immersive audio guide.
title: Tourists get to know Persepolis through a digital voyage

description: TEHRAN- Iranian director Oktay Baraheni’s “The Old Bachelor” will compete at the Transilvania International Film Festival, which will be held in Romania from June 14 to 23.
title: Transilvania film festival picks Oktay Baraheni’s “The Old Bachelor”

description: TEHRAN- “Un homme à distance” ("A Man at A Distance"), a book by French journalist and novelist Katherine Pancol, has recently been published in Persian.
title: "A Man at A Distance" published in Persian

description: TEHRAN- “Civil War”, a 2024 war drama by English director Alex Garland, was reviewed at the Arasbaran Cultural Center in Tehran on Wednesday.
title: Tehran cultural center reviews Alex Garland’s “Civil War”

description: TEHRAN-Seven cinematic works from Iran will participate in the 26th Shanghai International Film Festival (SIFF), set to be held in Shanghai, China, from June 14 to 23.
title: 26th Shanghai International Film Festival to screen seven Iranian films

description: TEHRAN - Shahrdari Gorgan booked their ticket to the Basketball Champions League Asia after securing a third-place finish in the FIBA West Asia Super League Final 8.
title: Gorgan beat Kuwait Club to advance to BCL Asia

description: Nikki Haley, former US envoy to the UN and former Republican candidate for the US 2024 presidential elections, has again drawn attention with her political support and closeness to Israel, which continues its attacks on Gaza, Anadolu Agency reports.
title: Pro-Israel former US envoy to UN in spotlight again for backing massacre in Gaza

description: TEHRAN –The National Organization for Migration is planning to implement an inclusive plan encompassing 40 projects to organize foreign nationals and refugees.
title: Over 40 projects to be implemented to organize foreign nationals

description: TEHRAN - A total of 513 earthquakes have been recorded across the country over the past calendar month that ended on May 19, according to the seismological networks of the Institute of Geophysics of the University of Tehran.
title: Almost 515 earthquakes occur in a month

description: TEHRAN –Over the past two years, the populations of Persian yellow deer, Persian zebras, jebeer gazelle, and gazelle have experienced a 35 percent growth in breeding centers, an official with the Department of Environment (DOE) has said.
title: Wildlife population grows by 35% in breeding centers

description: TEHRAN – Health Minister Bahram Einollahi has met some of his counterparts on the sidelines of the 77th World Health Assembly held in Geneva, Switzerland, exploring avenues to bolster collaborations in the health and medicine sector.
title: Iran boosts health diplomacy in Geneva

description: TEHRAN - Iran is set to inaugurate the Rasht-Caspian railway in the north of the country within the next few days, according to the Ministry of Transport and Urban Development.
title: Iran to launch Rasht-Caspian railway in coming days

description: TEHRAN – The Head of the National Petrochemical Company (NPC) Morteza Shahmirzaie says almost all of the need for petrochemical catalysts in the country is met by domestic producers, and the company is taking final steps to fully indigenize the knowledge for the production of such catalysts.
title: NPC taking final steps to localize petchem catalysts

description: TEHRAN - Following the upward trend of the past few days, TEDPIX the main index of the Tehran Stock Exchange (TSE) gained over 8,200 points on Saturday to stand at 2,094,284, IRNA reported.
title: TEDPIX gains 16,000 points on Wednesday

description: TEHRAN - Iran Chamber of Commerce, Industries, Mines and Agriculture (ICCIMA), Islamic Chamber Research and Information Center (ICRIC), and the Islamic Chamber Training Academy (ICTA) have signed a memorandum of understanding on developing human capabilities.
title: ICCIMA, ICTA sign MOU on human resources development

description: TEHRAN – Mehdi Saberi and Hossein Rasouli from Iran won two gold medals in the 4th MoC Grand Prix, underway in Lagos, Nigeria.
title: Iranian throwers Rasouli, Saberi win two golds at Nigerian Grand Prix

description: TEHRAN - The value of Iran’s non-oil trade reached $54.6 billion in the first two months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-May 21), according to the Islamic Republic of Iran Customs Administration (IRICA).
title: Iran’s non-oil trade exceeds $25b in 2 months

description: TEHRAN - Iran and Turkey have exchanged as much as $1.75 billion worth of goods in the first four months of 2024, according to a report by the Turkish Statistical Institute (TurkStat).
title: Iran-Turkey trade hits $1.75 billion in four months

description: TEHRAN - Electricity consumption in Iran increased by 11% or 6,000 megawatts (MW) in the previous Iranian calendar week (ended on May 31) compared to a week earlier, the head of Iran's Power Generation, Distribution, and Transmission Company (known as Tavanir) said.
title: Electricity consumption increases 11% as temperature begins to rise

description: TEHRAN – Iranian Pahlevani wrestler Mohammad Ramezani 19-Norandrosterone has been banned for three years after the athlete tested positive for a prohibited substance.
title: Iranian Pahlevani wrestler banned for doping
